###############################################################################
#   CONFIGURING TOOLS USED IN TESTS                                           #
###############################################################################

Paths to validation tools can be set in 'make.toolslocation.inc'

Not all paths have to be provided. If a path is missing, appropriate tool
will not be used in validation (it will be ignored if provided in config file

Providing paths to builds for HepMC2 allows to generate validation
benchmarks that can be compared against HepMC3. List of configuration
options used to build appropriate tools:

--------------
1) Photos++
--------------
wget http://photospp.web.cern.ch/photospp/resources/PHOTOS.3.54/PHOTOS.3.54.tar.gz
./configure --without-hepmc

with HepMC2:
./configure --with-hepmc=$HEPMC2LOCATION

--------------
2) Tauola++
--------------
wget http://tauolapp.web.cern.ch/tauolapp/resources/TAUOLA.1.1.4/TAUOLA.1.1.4.tar.gz
./configure --without-hepmc

with HepMC2:
./configure --with-hepmc=$HEPMC2LOCATION

-------------
3) Pythia8
-------------
wget http://home.thep.lu.se/~torbjorn/pythia8/pythia8185.tgz
./configure --enable-shared

with HepMC2:
./configure --enable-shared --with-hepmc=$HEPMC2LOCATION

NOTE: If compiled with HepMC2 - same directory can be used for HepMC2 and HepMC3

---------------
4) MC-TESTER
---------------
wget http://mc-tester.web.cern.ch/MC-TESTER/MC-TESTER-1.25.0.tar.gz

./configure

with HepMC2:
./configure --with-HepMC=$HEPMC2LOCATION

NOTE: If compiled with HepMC2 - same directory can be used for HepMC2 and HepMC3
